pull_request.title: feat: Allow public access to bytes
pull_request.body: When [building a protocol](https://github.com/Avarok-Cybersecurity/Citadel-Protocol/), we sometimes make use of generic bytes to allow variable use of subprotocols, and don't want to have to add the overhead of serialization. By allowing public access to the inner fields (whether directly or indirectly via a function), everything works.
